Package: PhyloIgSeq
Title: Immunoglobulin Coating and Diversity Analysis for 'phyloseq'
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Vladislav", "Antipin", , "Vladislav.Antipin@etu.sorbonne-universite.fr", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph")),
    person("Martin", "Larsen", role = c("aut", "ths", "cph")))
Description: Extends 'phyloseq' with tools for microbiota diversity analysis
    and immunoglobulin (Ig) coating quantification from 16S ribosomal RNA
    (rRNA) sequencing data. Provides a sparse-matrix engine for
    beta-diversity and UniFrac distances that scales to large amplicon
    sequence variant (ASV) tables without densifying the count matrix,
    classical and novel scoring methods (including a sliding Z-score) for
    IgSeq experiments with positive- and negative-sorted fractions, and
    approximate phylogenies built from taxonomic rank data when a
    sequencing-based tree is unavailable. Designed to support both direct
    analysis scripts and a companion 'shiny' web application.
